    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-11-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-11-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="196"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d196">
                <head>196. Memorandum for Record<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d196fn1">Source:
                        Central Intelligence Agency, Office of the Director for Science and
                        Technology, Job 33–02415A, Box 1, Folder 7. Top Secret. The memorandum was
                        handwritten by <persName corresp="#p_CGCP1">Cabell</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-11-19"
                        >November 19, 1954</date>.</dateline>
                <p>Following attended luncheon given by Secretary of Air Force, <persName
                        corresp="#p_THE1">Talbott</persName>: <list>
                        <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_GT1">Trevor Gardner</persName>, Asst. to
                                <gloss target="#t_SEC1">Sec</gloss>. A.F.</item>
                        <item>Lt. Gen. <persName>Donald Putt A.F.</persName>
                        </item>
                        <item>Dr. <persName corresp="#p_LEH1">Land</persName>
                        </item>
                        <item>Mr. <persName>Clarence Kelly Johnson</persName>, Lockheed A/C
                            Co.</item>
                        <item>Mr. <persName>Fred Ayers</persName>, Asst. to <gloss target="#t_SEC1"
                                >Sec</gloss>. A.F.</item>
                        <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_DAW1">Allen Dulles</persName>, <gloss
                                target="#t_DCI1">DCI</gloss>
                        </item>
                        <item>Lt. <persName corresp="#p_CGCP1">Gen. C.P. Cabell</persName>, <gloss
                                target="#t_DDCI1">DDCI</gloss>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>It was agreed that the special item of matériel described by Lockheed was
                    practical and desirable and would be sought in addition to the matériel item
                    suggested by <persName corresp="#p_TGNF1">Gen. Twining</persName> at the earlier
                    meeting with him.<note n="2" xml:id="d196fn2">The meeting has not been further
                        identified.</note>
                </p>
                <p>It was agreed that the Project should be a joint Air Force–<gloss
                        target="#t_CIA1">CIA</gloss> one but that regardless of the source of the
                    funds, whether A.F or <gloss target="#t_CIA1">CIA</gloss>, <gloss
                        target="#t_CIA1">CIA</gloss> unvouchered channels would be needed to pass
                    the funds.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>CPC</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
